    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Weathered Wood sits in the warm half of the asphalt spectrum and pairs naturally with brick, stone, and earth-tone siding. On Florida elevations with bright midday light, the surface picks up enough red to read as a clear, decided color rather than a generic 'dark roof'.",
      "The granule blend layers tobacco, amber, and dark walnut granules in a tight rotation. Up close you can see the layering; from the street it reads as one warm color with subtle texture.",
      "Works well with red brick, warm-wood accents, stone, and earth-tone paint. Tends to disagree with very cool siding colors (icy white, light blue, charcoal) where the warm undertone reads as out of place."
